cs.DB, cs.IR, cs.DS, cs.SI, cs.AI. 

The paper deals with a problem related to spatial databases, specifically the aggregation of spatial objects in streaming queries. Therefore, cs.DB (Databases) is the most likely category. The paper also proposes an approximation solution and an exact solution, which involves designing an index, indicating that it may fall under cs.IR (Information Retrieval) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). The paper also draws inspiration from rank aggregation and continuous queries, which could place it under cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence).
